FBIS3-52890 "drnes006_r_94011" FBIS-NES-94-006 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Jan 1994 India Minister Speaks of `Gains' of GATT Accord BK0801041294 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 GMT 8 Jan 94 BK0801041294 Delhi All India Radio Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The commerce minister, Mr. Pranab Kumar Mukherji, says the gains outweigh the likely disadvantages following the acceptance of the agreement on GATT talks. Speaking on the Dunkel proposals in Calcutta, he said multilateral arrangements widen the scope for trade. Mr. Mukherji said that subsidies given to farmers will not be discontinued as a result of the new agreement.
